(option "Influence" <Strength> args:{<amount> <type>}
 {
  (item "Standard Center Values" <0> <1>
   "Influence is calculated as the combined values of all stones within 1 step of the chosen location:
    
   Your stones count positive. 
   Enemy stones count negative. 
  
   According to the grid you are playing on, use the table below to determine the influence values for:
   -- the stone at the location itself ('Center'), and 
   -- the influence value for the stones one step away ('Adjacent'). 

--------------------------------------------
Table of Influence for the Different Grids
Grid Center Adjacent 
#3 ..... 0 ...... 2    -- Nodes of hexagon grid
#4 ..... 0 ...... 2    -- Nodes of square grid
#5 ..... 1 ...... 1    -- Nodes of snub-square grid (triangle-square grid)
#6 ..... 2 ...... 1    -- Nodes of triangular grid
#7 ..... 2 ...... 1    -- Nodes of snub-square grid (diagonal connections)
#8 ..... 3 ...... 1    -- Nodes of square grid (diagonal connections)

Note: These values are chosen to allow any stones between two friendly stones to be secure anywhere on the board for grids 3,5, 6, and  for three neighbor stones to be secure on grids 4,7, and 8.
This encourages formations with thin connections to the edge or between groups.

-------------------------------------------
   "
  )*
  (item "Boosted Center values" <1> <1>
   "Influence is calculated as the combined values of all stones within 1 step of the chosen location:
    
   Your stones count positive. 
   Enemy stones count negative. 
  
   From the table below, find the influence value of the center stone (if any) at the location, and the influence value for the stones one step away. 

--------------------------------------------
Table of Influence for the Different Grids
Grid Center Adjacent 
#3 ..... 2 ...... 2    -- Nodes of hexagon grid
#4 ..... 2 ...... 2    -- Nodes of square grid
#5 ..... 2 ...... 1    -- Nodes of snub-square grid (triangle-square grid)
#6 ..... 3 ...... 1    -- Nodes of triangular grid
#7 ..... 3 ...... 1    -- Nodes of snub-square grid (diagonal connections)
#8 ..... 4 ...... 1    -- Nodes of square grid (diagonal connections)

Note: These values are chosen to allow any stones between two friendly stones to be secure anywhere on the board for grids 3 through 8, and  for pairs to be safe on any edge.
This encourages edge invasions an formations with thin connections to the edge or between groups.
-------------------------------------------
   "
  )
  (item "Center Not Counted" <1> <-1>
   "Influence is calculated as the combined values of the stones that are 1 step away from the chosen location: 
   
   Your stones count positive. 
   Enemy stones count negative.  
   Do not include the contents of the location itself, if any.

This option means that an isolated stone next to an enemy can always be captured.
   ---------------------------------
   "
  )
  (item "Center Equal to Adjacent" <1> <0>
   "Influence is calculated as the combined values of all stones within 1 step of the chosen location: 
   
   Your stones count positive. 
   Enemy stones count negative. 
   Include the stone at the location itself, if any.
   ---------------------------------
   "
  )
 }
)

